                            <comment id="14113470" author="olvesh" created="Thu, 28 Aug 2014 07:25:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This has been annoying me for a while, and our ops guys got tripped by these large default values.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14140134" author="arodrime" created="Fri, 19 Sep 2014 07:21:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just to be sure to understand this correctly, If I set the stream throughput through nodetool, should I use Mb or MB ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14140423" author="olvesh" created="Fri, 19 Sep 2014 12:47:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Even though it says MB(yte) it really uses Mb(it).&lt;br/&gt;
I was a bit wrong though - compaction throughput is in MB, but stream is set in Mb.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Check e.g. org.apache.cassandra.db.compaction.CompactionManager#getRateLimiter&lt;br/&gt;
vs org.apache.cassandra.streaming.StreamManager.StreamRateLimiter#StreamRateLimiter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14155147" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2014 17:23:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=yukim&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;yukim&quot;&gt;yukim&lt;/a&gt; to review&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14156925" author="yukim" created="Thu, 2 Oct 2014 18:19:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Olve, and yes, compaction throughput is in MByte/s, so I removed the change for it from your patch.&lt;br/&gt;
I committed streaming throughput change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
